<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Inglewood</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Inglewood is Calgary’s oldest area and it oozes old-world charm mixed with modern chic.
                Homes in Inglewood were once neighbours to second hand shops and purveyors of antiques. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Inglewood real estate has a rich history and has now become neighbour to the newest fine
                restaurant and design district. Transformed by an influx of fine restaurants and trendy services
                Inglewood is a unique and complimentary variation of cheap to chic. </p>
            <p class="par-xl">Spend the day in Inglewood enjoying gorgeous scenery and relaxing on the riverfront. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Visit some of Calgary’s and Canada’s top ranked restaurants such as Rouge. Miles of tree
                lined paths, spacious parks, the Bow River, playgrounds and sports fields. Inglewood is the perfect
                place for year round active living.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Inglewood is located in Ward 9 and represented by Gian-Carlo Carra on the Calgary City
                Council. Provincially, Inglewood is in the Calgary-Fort riding, represented by Wayne Cao and federally
                in the Calgary-Southeast riding, represented by Jason Kenney.</p>


        </div>
